\begin{enumerate}
    \item How many batches of cookies can Sarah bake with the 4 cups of flour she has?
    \item Suppose Sarah's cousin also wants to bake cookies and has $\frac{7}{2}$ cups of flour, using the same recipe. Who can bake more batches of cookies with their available flour? Arrange Sarah's and her cousin's possible number of batches in ascending order.
\end{enumerate}

response_dict.solution:
\textbf{(1) Number of batches Sarah can bake:}

Number of batches $= \dfrac{4}{\frac{2}{3}} = 4 \times \frac{3}{2} = 2 \times 3 = 6$

Sarah can bake \textbf{6 batches} of cookies.

\textbf{(2) Number of batches Sarah's cousin can bake:}

Her cousin has $\frac{7}{2}$ cups of flour.

