So, Sarah can bake $6$ batches and her cousin can bake $5\frac{1}{4}$ batches.

\textbf{Arranging in ascending order:}

$5\frac{1}{4} < 6$

So, Sarah's cousin can bake fewer batches than Sarah.

\textbf{Final Answer:}
\begin{itemize}
    \item Sarah can bake $6$ batches, cousin can bake $5\frac{1}{4}$ batches.
    \item In ascending order: $5\frac{1}{4}$, $6$.
\end{itemize}

